Stamp tax increases will be imposed on those who do not pay taxes in the UK
The Treasury expects the tax to raise up to 120 million pounds a year to help the homeless.
Foreign buyers will be charged a higher rate of stamp tax when buying a property in the UK - the extra revenue will be used to help the homeless, Theresa May will announce today.
The move was seen as an attempt to counteract Jeremy Corbyn's move to attract young voters, with promises to provide cheaper housing and focus on high-income earners.
The stamp tax will be levied on individuals and companies who do not pay taxes in the UK, and the additional revenue will strengthen the government's move to help those who are sleeping in difficult conditions.
